<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="237" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="30.[178,1085,362,413]" pageId="30" pageNumber="237">Etymology: The specific epithet (Latin, adjective: carrying a protuberance) alludes to the pronounced median granule of the male tergite III.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="237" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="30.[178,1085,428,596]" pageId="30" pageNumber="237">
Description: Body length 
<quantity box="[547,671,428,449]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" metricValueMax="4.8" metricValueMin="3.8" pageId="30" pageNumber="237" unit="mm" value="4.3" valueMax="4.8" valueMin="3.8">3.8-4.8 mm</quantity>
; length of forebody 
<quantity box="[890,1014,428,449]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" metricValueMax="2.1" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="30" pageNumber="237" unit="mm" value="1.9" valueMax="2.1" valueMin="1.7">1.7-2.1 mm</quantity>
. Coloration: head and pronotum blackish-brown to blackish; elytra dark-yellowish to brown, with the scutellar region and the postero-lateral angles diffusely and more or less extensively darker; abdomen dark-brown to blackish-brown, with the posterior margins of the segments reddish; legs dark-yellowish; antennae blackish-brown to blackish, with antennomere I yellowish-brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[178,1086,612,751]" pageId="30" pageNumber="237">
Head (
<figureCitation box="[246,332,612,634]" captionStart="Figs 106-116" captionStartId="31.[178,218,1461,1483]" captionTargetBox="[178,1076,212,1435]" captionTargetId="figure-1@31.[178,1082,212,1452]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Figs 106-116: Nepalota tuberifera nov.sp.: (106) forebody; (107) antenna; (108) anterior portion of male abdomen; (109) male tergite VIII; (110) male sternite VIII; (111) posterior margin of male tergite VIII; (112-113) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (114) female tergite VIII; (115) female sternite VIII; (116) spermatheca. Scale bars: 106-110, 114-115: 0.5 mm; 112- 113, 116: 0.2 mm; 111: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414212" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414212/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="237">Fig. 106</figureCitation>
) transverse, approximately 1.1 times as broad as long; dorsal surface with distinct microreticulation; punctation moderately dense and fine. Eyes large, much longer than postocular region in dorsal view. Antenna (
<figureCitation box="[700,792,670,692]" captionStart="Figs 106-116" captionStartId="31.[178,218,1461,1483]" captionTargetBox="[178,1076,212,1435]" captionTargetId="figure-1@31.[178,1082,212,1452]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Figs 106-116: Nepalota tuberifera nov.sp.: (106) forebody; (107) antenna; (108) anterior portion of male abdomen; (109) male tergite VIII; (110) male sternite VIII; (111) posterior margin of male tergite VIII; (112-113) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (114) female tergite VIII; (115) female sternite VIII; (116) spermatheca. Scale bars: 106-110, 114-115: 0.5 mm; 112- 113, 116: 0.2 mm; 111: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414212" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414212/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="237">Fig. 107</figureCitation>
) slender, 
<quantity box="[901,1022,670,692]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="30" pageNumber="237" unit="mm" value="1.45" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.4">1.4-1.5 mm</quantity>
long; antennomere IV oblong; preapical antennomeres very weakly transverse or as long as broad; antennomere XI apically acute, longer than the combined length of IX and X.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[178,1086,766,847]" pageId="30" pageNumber="237">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[293,380,766,788]" captionStart="Figs 106-116" captionStartId="31.[178,218,1461,1483]" captionTargetBox="[178,1076,212,1435]" captionTargetId="figure-1@31.[178,1082,212,1452]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Figs 106-116: Nepalota tuberifera nov.sp.: (106) forebody; (107) antenna; (108) anterior portion of male abdomen; (109) male tergite VIII; (110) male sternite VIII; (111) posterior margin of male tergite VIII; (112-113) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (114) female tergite VIII; (115) female sternite VIII; (116) spermatheca. Scale bars: 106-110, 114-115: 0.5 mm; 112- 113, 116: 0.2 mm; 111: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414212" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414212/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="237">Fig. 106</figureCitation>
) approximately 1.2 times as broad as long and 1.3 times as broad as head, without sexual dimorphism; disc with distinct microreticulation; punctation dense and moderately fine, more distinct than that of head.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[178,1085,862,913]" pageId="30" pageNumber="237">
Elytra (
<figureCitation box="[257,347,862,884]" captionStart="Figs 106-116" captionStartId="31.[178,218,1461,1483]" captionTargetBox="[178,1076,212,1435]" captionTargetId="figure-1@31.[178,1082,212,1452]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Figs 106-116: Nepalota tuberifera nov.sp.: (106) forebody; (107) antenna; (108) anterior portion of male abdomen; (109) male tergite VIII; (110) male sternite VIII; (111) posterior margin of male tergite VIII; (112-113) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (114) female tergite VIII; (115) female sternite VIII; (116) spermatheca. Scale bars: 106-110, 114-115: 0.5 mm; 112- 113, 116: 0.2 mm; 111: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414212" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414212/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="237">Fig. 106</figureCitation>
) slightly longer than pronotum; punctation very dense and fine; interstices with microreticulation. Hind wings fully developed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[178,1085,928,980]" pageId="30" pageNumber="237">Abdomen with very shallow transverse microsculpture; punctation sparse and fine; tergites III and VII with sexual dimorphism.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[178,1086,995,1193]" pageId="30" pageNumber="237">
♂: tergite III with pronounced median protuberance at posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[978,1073,995,1017]" captionStart="Figs 106-116" captionStartId="31.[178,218,1461,1483]" captionTargetBox="[178,1076,212,1435]" captionTargetId="figure-1@31.[178,1082,212,1452]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Figs 106-116: Nepalota tuberifera nov.sp.: (106) forebody; (107) antenna; (108) anterior portion of male abdomen; (109) male tergite VIII; (110) male sternite VIII; (111) posterior margin of male tergite VIII; (112-113) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (114) female tergite VIII; (115) female sternite VIII; (116) spermatheca. Scale bars: 106-110, 114-115: 0.5 mm; 112- 113, 116: 0.2 mm; 111: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414212" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414212/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="237">Fig. 108</figureCitation>
); tergite VII with weakly pronounced median elevation, this elevation with denser punctation and more distinct microreticulation; tergite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[741,887,1054,1076]" captionStart="Figs 106-116" captionStartId="31.[178,218,1461,1483]" captionTargetBox="[178,1076,212,1435]" captionTargetId="figure-1@31.[178,1082,212,1452]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Figs 106-116: Nepalota tuberifera nov.sp.: (106) forebody; (107) antenna; (108) anterior portion of male abdomen; (109) male tergite VIII; (110) male sternite VIII; (111) posterior margin of male tergite VIII; (112-113) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (114) female tergite VIII; (115) female sternite VIII; (116) spermatheca. Scale bars: 106-110, 114-115: 0.5 mm; 112- 113, 116: 0.2 mm; 111: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414212" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414212/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="237">Figs 109, 111</figureCitation>
) with truncate and crenulate posterior margin; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[608,697,1083,1105]" captionStart="Figs 106-116" captionStartId="31.[178,218,1461,1483]" captionTargetBox="[178,1076,212,1435]" captionTargetId="figure-1@31.[178,1082,212,1452]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Figs 106-116: Nepalota tuberifera nov.sp.: (106) forebody; (107) antenna; (108) anterior portion of male abdomen; (109) male tergite VIII; (110) male sternite VIII; (111) posterior margin of male tergite VIII; (112-113) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (114) female tergite VIII; (115) female sternite VIII; (116) spermatheca. Scale bars: 106-110, 114-115: 0.5 mm; 112- 113, 116: 0.2 mm; 111: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414212" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414212/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="237">Fig. 110</figureCitation>
) slightly longer than tergite VIII and strongly convex posteriorly; median lobe of aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[737,873,1112,1134]" captionStart="Figs 106-116" captionStartId="31.[178,218,1461,1483]" captionTargetBox="[178,1076,212,1435]" captionTargetId="figure-1@31.[178,1082,212,1452]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Figs 106-116: Nepalota tuberifera nov.sp.: (106) forebody; (107) antenna; (108) anterior portion of male abdomen; (109) male tergite VIII; (110) male sternite VIII; (111) posterior margin of male tergite VIII; (112-113) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (114) female tergite VIII; (115) female sternite VIII; (116) spermatheca. Scale bars: 106-110, 114-115: 0.5 mm; 112- 113, 116: 0.2 mm; 111: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414212" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414212/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="237">Figs 112-113</figureCitation>
) approximately 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="30" pageNumber="237" unit="mm" value="0.55">0.55 mm</quantity>
long; ventral process and internal structures of distinctive shapes; paramere longer than median lobe and with moderately slender apical lobe.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[178,1086,1208,1259]" pageId="30" pageNumber="237">
<specimenCount box="[178,199,1214,1235]" pageId="30" pageNumber="237" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
: tergite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[349,438,1208,1230]" captionStart="Figs 106-116" captionStartId="31.[178,218,1461,1483]" captionTargetBox="[178,1076,212,1435]" captionTargetId="figure-1@31.[178,1082,212,1452]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Figs 106-116: Nepalota tuberifera nov.sp.: (106) forebody; (107) antenna; (108) anterior portion of male abdomen; (109) male tergite VIII; (110) male sternite VIII; (111) posterior margin of male tergite VIII; (112-113) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (114) female tergite VIII; (115) female sternite VIII; (116) spermatheca. Scale bars: 106-110, 114-115: 0.5 mm; 112- 113, 116: 0.2 mm; 111: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414212" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414212/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="237">Fig. 114</figureCitation>
) with moderately convex posterior margin; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs 106-116" captionStartId="31.[178,218,1461,1483]" captionTargetBox="[178,1076,212,1435]" captionTargetId="figure-1@31.[178,1082,212,1452]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Figs 106-116: Nepalota tuberifera nov.sp.: (106) forebody; (107) antenna; (108) anterior portion of male abdomen; (109) male tergite VIII; (110) male sternite VIII; (111) posterior margin of male tergite VIII; (112-113) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (114) female tergite VIII; (115) female sternite VIII; (116) spermatheca. Scale bars: 106-110, 114-115: 0.5 mm; 112- 113, 116: 0.2 mm; 111: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414212" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414212/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="237">Fig. 115</figureCitation>
) broadly convex posteriorly; spermatheca (
<figureCitation box="[657,744,1237,1259]" captionStart="Figs 106-116" captionStartId="31.[178,218,1461,1483]" captionTargetBox="[178,1076,212,1435]" captionTargetId="figure-1@31.[178,1082,212,1452]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Figs 106-116: Nepalota tuberifera nov.sp.: (106) forebody; (107) antenna; (108) anterior portion of male abdomen; (109) male tergite VIII; (110) male sternite VIII; (111) posterior margin of male tergite VIII; (112-113) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (114) female tergite VIII; (115) female sternite VIII; (116) spermatheca. Scale bars: 106-110, 114-115: 0.5 mm; 112- 113, 116: 0.2 mm; 111: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414212" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414212/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="237">Fig. 116</figureCitation>
) approximately 
<quantity box="[910,987,1237,1259]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="30" pageNumber="237" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="237" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="30.[178,1085,1282,1451]" pageId="30" pageNumber="237">
Comparative notes: This species is characterized particularly by the pronounced protuberance of the male tergite III and the shape of the aedeagus. The similar modifications of the male tergites III and VII, as well as the similar general morphology of the aedeagus suggest that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2015" box="[474,605,1370,1392]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Nepalota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberifera">
<emphasis box="[474,605,1370,1392]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="237">N. tuberifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely allied to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2015" box="[807,926,1371,1392]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Nepalota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martensi">
<emphasis box="[807,926,1371,1392]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="237">N. martensi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. For characters distinguishing this species from the highly similar 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2015" box="[724,863,1400,1421]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Nepalota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prominula">
<emphasis box="[724,863,1400,1421]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="237">N. prominula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see the comparative notes in the following section.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="237" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="30.[178,1085,1474,1555]" pageId="30" pageNumber="237">
Distribution and natural history: The specimens were collected in three localities in the southern Gaoligong 
<collectingRegion box="[645,698,1503,1525]" country="Myanmar" name="Shan" pageId="30" pageNumber="237">Shan</collectingRegion>
, western 
<collectingRegion box="[798,878,1504,1525]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="30" pageNumber="237">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[894,964,1503,1525]" captionStart="Map 6" captionStartId="32.[178,223,877,898]" captionTargetBox="[178,1082,212,868]" captionTargetId="figure-1@32.[178,1082,212,868]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="Map 6: Distributions of Nepalota globifera PACE (filled circles: examined records; open circle: literature record), N. tuberifera nov.sp. (open stars), N. prominula nov.sp. (open diamond), and N. daweiana nov.sp. (filled triangle) in China." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414214" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414214/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="237">Map 6</figureCitation>
), by sifting leaf litter in deciduous and degraded primary forests at altitudes of 
<quantity box="[858,996,1533,1554]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.55" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.1" pageId="30" pageNumber="237" unit="m" value="2550.0" valueMax="3000.0" valueMin="2100.0">2100-3000 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
